CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1955, pg. 31, reads: "NIADA Members Satisfy - Typical of the many customers who are satisfied with their purchases from members of the National Independent Automobile Dealers Association is Edward Lee, a construction worker, of 7513 Bennett Street, whose family has purchased four good used cars from the M & W Motor Sales, 3925 Forbes Street, whose owner, Lenny Weisenberg, is treasurer of the Western Pennsylvania Independent Automobile Dealers Association. - Harris Photo."image also published in advertistment in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1955, pg. 32.
TitMainTitle: Lenny Weisenberg shaking hands with Edward Lee wearing hat, standing in M. & W. Motor Sales car lot with two billboards reading "'Nuff Said Duquesne Beer," and "Let's continue the best County Government we've ever had! Re-elect Commissioners John J. Kane and Harry W. Fowler Vote straight Democratic X,"  3925 Forbes Avenue
